    {
      "title": "Form X Verbs (اِسْتَفْعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل في الباب العاشر",
      "content": [
        "Form X verbs follow the pattern اِسْتَفْعَلَ - يَسْتَفْعِلُ. This form typically indicates seeking, requesting, or considering something to have a quality.",
        "The prefix اِسْتَـ is the distinguishing feature of this form."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Past pattern: اِسْتَفْعَلَ (e.g., اِسْتَغْفَرَ)",
        "Present pattern: يَسْتَفْعِلُ (e.g., يَسْتَغْفِرُ)",
        "Meanings: Seeking, requesting, considering as",
        "غَفَرَ (to forgive) → اِسْتَغْفَرَ (to seek forgiveness)",
        "أَذِنَ (to permit) → اِسْتَأْذَنَ (to ask permission)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَغْفَرَ اللهَ", "english": "He sought forgiveness from Allah" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَأْذَنَ قَبْلَ الدُّخُولِ", "english": "He asked permission before entering" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَخْدَمَ الْحَاسُوبَ", "english": "He used the computer" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَقْبَلَ الضُّيُوفَ", "english": "He welcomed the guests" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Form X Verbs",
      "titleArabic": "أفعال شائعة من الباب العاشر",
      "content": [
        "Form X contains many frequently used verbs in modern and classical Arabic."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "اِسْتَغْفَرَ (to seek forgiveness)",
        "اِسْتَأْذَنَ (to ask permission)",
        "اِسْتَخْدَمَ (to use/employ)",
        "اِسْتَفْهَمَ (to inquire)",
        "اِسْتَقْبَلَ (to receive/welcome)",
        "اِسْتَعْمَلَ (to use)"
      ]
    }
